The paper deals with multirobot coordination and planning trajectories to satisfy high-level specifications, which are common topics in robotics (cs.RO) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of temporal logics to express these specifications suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the logic (cs.LO) and programming languages (cs.PL) sub-categories. Finally, the paper's focus on generating trajectories that can be executed synchronously or asynchronously suggests that it may also be relevant to the systems and control (cs.SY) sub-category.
